[3]
Date: Fri 10 Jan 2003
From: A-Lan Banks <A-Lan.Banks@derwent.co.uk>
Source: Keralanext, Fri 10 Jan 2003 [edited]
<http://www.keralanext.com/news/index.asp?id=5720>

India: dengue fever cases and 2 deaths reported from Kerala
-----------------------------------------------------------
At least 2 people have died, while 18 tested positive for dengue fever in
this district of Kerala in the past 3 months. District medical officer K
Shailaja told reporters on Thu 9 Jan 2003 that steps were being taken on a
war-footing to contain the mosquito menace in the affected areas of this
district.
She said task forces had been constituted at the district, block, and
panchayat levels to coordinate various activities like fogging, spraying of
insecticides, and source reduction in cooperation with the public,
voluntary organizations, and residential associations.
--
